Poly Archives at the Bern Dibner Library of Science and Technology, NYU Libraries
Poly Archives Serial Publications Collection RG.030 32
69 Linear Feet (11 boxes and approximately 250 bound volumes)
1884-2014 Bern Dibner Library of Science and Technology 5 MetroTech Center Brooklyn, New York, 11201 (646) 997-3943 polyarchives@nyu.edu
Conditions Governing Access
Open for research without restrictions.
Conditions Governing Use
Any rights (including copyright and related rights to publicity and privacy) held by Polytechnic University in all its forms are maintained by New York University. Permission to publish or reproduce materials in this collection must be secured from the Poly Archives. Please contact the Poly Archives, polyarchives@nyu.edu, 646-997-3530.
Preferred Citation
Identification of item, date; Poly Archives Serial Publications Collection; RG 030; box number; folder number or item identifier; Poly Archives at Bern Dibner Library of Science and Technology, New York University.
Arrangement
The series are arranged alphabetically by publication title.
Biographical / Historical
The serial publications in this collection were loosely grouped together in the archives in the mid 2000s. Historical notes at the series level provide an explanation of each publication in this collection.
Scope and Contents
The publications in this collection include newsletters, bulletins, newspapers, department news, yearbooks, alumni magazines and literary journals. Collectively, these publications produced by Polytechnic students, faculty, alumni, and the administration, cover over 100 years of research, innovation, and campus life.
Immediate Source of Acquisition
Materials found in collection; there is no documentation concerning the provenance of these materials.

Biographical / Historical
The Polytechnic Engineer was a technical magazine, founded in 1898, for undergraduate students at Polytechnic. The magazine included student articles on engineering and science as well as current research at the school. The publication lay dormant for forty years, when it was resurrected in 1960 with a new volume 1.

Biographical / Historical
The Polytechnic News bulletin underwent slight title and audience changes over the years, but remained a widely distributed source of information about faculty research and happenings around Polytechnic. From 1955-1956 the bulletins were titled "Report from Polytechnic Institute of Brooklyn." In 1957, the headline changed to "News from Polytechnic: A newsletter for the faculty in staff." In 1970, this title was tweaked to "The Polytechnic Faculty News: For faculty and staff of the Polytechnic Institute of Brooklyn." In 1974, the title changed to "Polytechnic News: A Newsletter of Polytechnic Institute of New York," which indicated both the university's name change and, no longer specifying faculty as the only audience, a wider distribution. In 1984 the title became "Poly News: Polytechnic Institute of New York - Newsletter - Brooklyn - Long island - Westchester." Finally, in 1986, reflecting yet another name change to the university, the title changed to "Poly News: Polytechnic University - Newsletter - Brooklyn - Long island - Westchester."
